<h2>II.Â Configure Guided Access to Lock an App or Website</h2>
<ol>
	<li>Open the <strong>app</strong> you'd like to lock in kiosk mode (we're using <a href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/" target="_blank">SurveyMonkey</a>Â in these screenshots).</li>
	<li><strong>Triple-click</strong>Â the iPad home button while in the app. This will activate <strong>Guided Access</strong>.</li>
	<li><span><strong>Triple-click</strong><span>Â the iPad home button again and enter your password toÂ </span>open the </span><strong>Guided Access menu.</strong></li>
	<li>Tap onÂ <strong><em>Hardware Buttons</em></strong>Â to enable/disable the sleep/wake button, <span>volume buttons, motion, and keyboards</span>.</li>
	<li>Tap onÂ <strong><em>TouchÂ </em></strong>to enable/disable touch functions. (Disabling touch will turn your iPad into a view-only device.)</li>
	<li>You can also disable any portion of the screen by circling it while in the Guided Access menu. (This is helpful when you want to disable a button, link, or the address bar of a web browser, for example.)</li>
	<li>Tap on <strong><em>Time Limit</em>Â </strong>to set a time limit for using the app. Once the limit is reached, the user will be prompted to re-enter the password.</li>
	<li>When finished, tap on <strong><em>Resume</em></strong>Â to activate Guided Access. You're now in "kiosk mode"!</li>
	<li>To <strong>Exit</strong> kiosk mode, <strong>Triple-click</strong> the iPad home button, enter your Guided Access passcode and tap <strong><em>End</em></strong> in the top left.</li>
</ol>
